ZH: 戏剧是一种表演艺术形式。
EN: Drama is a form of performing arts.

ZH: 这部电影是根据一个戏剧改编的。
EN: This movie is adapted from a play.

ZH: 我们在学校一起演了一出戏剧。
EN: We performed a play together at school.

ZH: 我对戏剧表演很感兴趣。
EN: I am very interested in drama performance.

ZH: 这场戏剧演出非常精彩。
EN: The drama performance was very impressive.

ZH: 我们经常去观看不同风格的戏剧。
EN: We often go to see different styles of plays.

ZH: 我们的学校每年都会举办一场大型戏剧节。
EN: Our school organizes a large drama festival every year.

ZH: 她是一位才华横溢的戏剧演员。
EN: She is a talented drama actress.

ZH: 这部戏剧引起了观众的热烈反响。
EN: This play received a warm response from the audience.

ZH: 我们班的同学正在练习一部现代戏剧。
EN: The students in our class are practicing a modern play.

ZH: 这个剧团每年都会演一出经典戏剧。
EN: This theater troupe performs a classic play every year.

ZH: 她正在学习戏剧排练的技巧。
EN: She is learning the techniques of drama rehearsals.

ZH: 戏剧是我最喜欢的艺术形式之一。
EN: Drama is one of my favorite forms of art.

ZH: 戏剧可以传达深刻的情感。
EN: Drama can convey profound emotions.

ZH: 我们要扮演戏剧中的不同角色。
EN: We have to play different roles in the drama.

ZH: 戏剧可以让人们感受到不同的文化。
EN: Drama can make people experience different cultures.

ZH: 我们正在研究古典希腊戏剧。
EN: We are studying classical Greek drama.

ZH: 戏剧可以引发人们的思考。
EN: Drama can provoke people's thoughts.

ZH: 我们的初步排练已经开始了戏剧。
EN: Our initial rehearsals for the play have started.

ZH: 戏剧不仅仅是演员们的表演，还有舞台设计、服装和音乐。
EN: Drama is not just about the actors' performance, but also about stage design, costumes, and music.
